COLOR (in ethanol). Carapace ochre-yellow, with slightly darker median band including ocular area; clypeus not darkened; sternum ochre-yellow with brown speckles; legs ochre-yellow, without darker rings, with black spots (rather than lines) on femora and (few) on tibiae (cf. 
Figs 709–710
); abdomen pale gray, with dark lines around heart area and posterior median mark; ventrally with distinct black pattern (disrupted median band).
